{"type":"data","nodes":[{"type":"data","data":[null],"uses":{}},{"type":"data","data":[{"libraryName":1,"itemPath":2,"docItem":3},"sveltejs-svelte","Styling/nested-style-elements",{"type":4,"path":5,"relevant":6,"token_counts":7,"usage":11,"markdown":15},"page","04-styling/04-nested-style-elements.md",true,{"fulltext":8,"digest":9,"short_digest":10},167,144,85,{"input":12,"output":13,"details":14},1208,333,null,{"fulltext":16,"digest":17,"short_digest":18,"essence":19},"---\ntitle: Nested \u003Cstyle> elements\n---\n\nThere can only be one top-level `\u003Cstyle>` tag per component.\n\nHowever, it is possible to have a `\u003Cstyle>` tag nested inside other elements or logic blocks.\n\nIn that case, the `\u003Cstyle>` tag will be inserted as-is into the DOM; no scoping or processing will be done on the `\u003Cstyle>` tag.\n\n```svelte\n\u003Cdiv>\n\t\u003Cstyle>\n\t\t/* this style tag will be inserted as-is */\n\t\tdiv {\n\t\t\t/* this will apply to all `\u003Cdiv>` elements in the DOM */\n\t\t\tcolor: red;\n\t\t}\n\t\u003C/style>\n\u003C/div>\n```\n","A component can only have one top-level `\u003Cstyle>` tag. However, you can place `\u003Cstyle>` tags nested inside other elements or logic blocks. When nested, the style tag is inserted as-is into the DOM without any scoping or processing applied.\n\n```svelte\n\u003Cdiv>\n\t\u003Cstyle>\n\t\tdiv {\n\t\t\tcolor: red;\n\t\t}\n\t\u003C/style>\n\u003C/div>\n```\n\nIn this example, the nested `\u003Cstyle>` tag will apply to all `\u003Cdiv>` elements in the entire DOM, not just the component, since no scoping is performed on nested styles.","Only one top-level `\u003Cstyle>` tag per component is allowed. Nested `\u003Cstyle>` tags inside elements or logic blocks are inserted as-is without scoping, so they affect the entire DOM.\n\n```svelte\n\u003Cdiv>\n\t\u003Cstyle>\n\t\tdiv { color: red; }\n\t\u003C/style>\n\u003C/div>\n```","Nested style tags bypass component scoping and apply globally to the DOM."],"uses":{"params":["name","path"]}}]}
